INSERT INTO `weekly_horoscope` VALUES (1,'2022-12-01','week5',8,'horoscope','content1'),(2,'2023-01-01','week1',8,'horoscope','content2'),(3,'2023-01-01','week2',8,'horoscope','content3'),(4,'2022-12-21','week 1',1,'horoscope','This week, a sudden epiphany helps you focus on a worthy goal.<br>The week begins on Monday, December 19, with Venus in Capricorn at the top of your chart making a quincunx to Mars in Gemini and your house of communication. You’re not often concerned with what other people think. Except for today. Now you feel like you need to make concessions for someone else. Aries, you have to step aside as they sashay by. This might be a particular coworker who has caused you trouble in the past. Today, they are particularly irritating, but this isn’t a good day to pick a fight.<br>On Wednesday, December 21, the sun in Sagittarius and your house of wisdom squares Jupiter in Pisces. A sudden and amazing epiphany might knock you off your feet. New wisdom is pouring into your brain, and suddenly you see your life very differently. Aries, it’s like the light switch has been flicked on and the darkness has disappeared.'),(5,'2022-12-21','week 1',1,'horoscope','It\'s gonna be all Aries, all the time, starting Tuesday, December 20, when expansive, auspicious and all-around joy-inducing Jupiter circles back to your sign for the second of its two game-changing transits.<br>You already got a taste of this energy from May 10 to October 28, when the bountiful planet took the first of its two laps through Aries. But once Jupiter returned to Pisces for its last “hurrah,” buried emotions resurfaced, forcing you to put up some serious boundaries. It’s been draining but also necessary. Now for the REALLY good news. The lucky, larger-than-life planet returns to Aries until May 16, 2023, giving you six months to keep zooming ahead with its rocket fuel in your tanks. Starting this Tuesday, you are officially on notice that dreams can no longer be deferred, and anything and everything you\'ve been hoping to accomplish in your life is now on the table. Personal growth? Bucket-list travel experiences? Fame and fortune? Bring it! This rare transit is not something you want to ignore. Over the next six months, you are invited—make that required—to shake up your life, shuck off any limitations or self-doubt and start taking steps toward becoming the person you want to be and creating the life you crave.<br>Bear in mind that Jupiter offers the possibility and holds the door open, but you\'ve got to do the heavy lifting—and also take the gamble to walk through that portal when the gifts arrive. While Jupiter transits certainly bring chances and connections and inspiration, you need to face your fears, take some risks and put yourself out there. No matter what your craft or superpower, unleash your trailblazing nature and give your passions top billing. Jupiter\'s energy is generous, though, so even as you\'re advancing your own mission, you\'ll realize it\'s not a zero-sum game. Chiron, the wounded healer comet, is also making a positive pivot on Friday, ending a five-month retrograde through Aries. With these two celestial sages in your corner, the message will be clear: Giving your best self to the world is the fastest way to gain in return.<br>With so many exciting plans bubbling, it will be hard to choose just one. (#AriesProblems) But you\'re at your best when you focus your considerable motivation in a clear direction instead of scattering far and wide. Lucky for you, this Wednesday, December 21, the Sun sweeps into single-minded (and insanely ambitious) Capricorn, putting you in your goal-oriented element until January 20, 2023. Two days later, on the 23rd, the Capricorn new moon—a potent supermoon—arrives to give this energy a giant lift. Yes, it may be the holiday season, but you’ve got big plans, Aries—and in typical Ram fashion, you can’t wait to get going on them. With the moon hanging out in Capricorn until early Christmas Day, you won’t be able to stop yourself from talking at least a LITTLE bit of shop around the tree.<br>Try to pace yourself though! Even your impulsive sign will feel the influence of the celestial Sea Goat\'s steady approach to building. In between gift-wrapping (and unwrapping), sit down to do some planning. Start by mapping out your quest, complete with a timeline, a list of what you need and the great minds you may want to tap as co-conspirators. If a business plan is needed, tap a pro to help you with that, or find a template that can help you structure your thoughts. Of course, no one said you have to do all this from home base. You may find way more inspiration on a lanai overlooking the sea or in front of a roaring fire at an upscale ski lodge.'),(6,'2022-12-21','week 1',1,'horoscope','It\'s gonna be all Aries, all the time, starting Tuesday, December 20, when expansive, auspicious and all-around joy-inducing Jupiter circles back to your sign for the second of its two game-changing transits.<br>You already got a taste of this energy from May 10 to October 28, when the bountiful planet took the first of its two laps through Aries. But once Jupiter returned to Pisces for its last “hurrah,” buried emotions resurfaced, forcing you to put up some serious boundaries. It’s been draining but also necessary. Now for the REALLY good news. The lucky, larger-than-life planet returns to Aries until May 16, 2023, giving you six months to keep zooming ahead with its rocket fuel in your tanks. Starting this Tuesday, you are officially on notice that dreams can no longer be deferred, and anything and everything you\'ve been hoping to accomplish in your life is now on the table. Personal growth? Bucket-list travel experiences? Fame and fortune? Bring it! This rare transit is not something you want to ignore. Over the next six months, you are invited—make that required—to shake up your life, shuck off any limitations or self-doubt and start taking steps toward becoming the person you