wds at the big box store, where the line to get in the parking lot snakes around the block. Today, you are nothing but determined.'),(29,'2022-12-21','week 1',7,'horoscope','No, it’s not breaking news that Libras thrive in healthy partnerships. But more than most signs, you run the risk of getting lost in the couple bubble, yielding your identity to the “us” you want the world to see. And that’s when your mood can take a stormy turn. Preventative care is on its way this Tuesday, December 20, as indie-spirited Jupiter bounds back into Aries for the second of two laps through your seventh house of relationships. Until May 16, 2023, you’ll be busy solving this riddle: How can I discover MORE of myself by combining forces with others? Here’s a clue: It begins with bringing MORE Libra to the table. Not just for display purposes (though you do look gooood!), but in order to share your offerings in an interactive way. Jupiter in Aries can bring out everyone’s performative energy, which can be fun for adding sizzle and glamour. But make sure you’re not raising the bar so high that people feel intimidated or exhausted by your expectations. Conversely, if you’ve been stuck in the role of the helpful sounding board, plug in your mic and start adding to the conversation. Consider yourself enrolled in a six-month master class that teaches you the fine art of “give and take.”<br>You may have already teamed up with a promising plus-one when Jupiter landed in Aries this past May 10. But on July 28, the philosophical planet turned retrograde, spinning back through this zone until October 28. An easy-breezy duo may have taken a complex turn. Perhaps your interest in forging ahead with a certain someone faded away. Certain relationships may be done and over with, but have you closed them out with the grace you desire? If you’ve both gone to your respective corners and done your “work,” you may finally be able to say a painful, but loving, goodbye. Libras who are in the dating game wil