 moving into your home zone on Wednesday. Especially if you have nitpicky family coming over. It’s also an ideal time to buy a new home or add another member to your family.<br>Friday is family night during the new moon in Capricorn. This is a great time to have your support system around you as you enjoy some of your favorite holiday traditions or even start some new ones. Feel the love, Libra!'),(31,'2022-12-21','week 2',7,'horoscope','This week, you’re going within to find the truth.<br>On Tuesday, December 27, Venus in Capricorn and your house of family makes a semisextile to Saturn in Aquarius and your house of children and younger relatives. Today, the focus is on children. You could be visiting the kids of your extended family, including cousins, nieces, and nephews. Libra, you might help a relative who is pregnant or has recently given birth. Today, you’re around the younger generation.<br>On Wednesday, December 28, Venus sextiles Neptune in Pisces and your house of health and well-being. Today, you could immerse yourself in mindful meditation. Libra, you might balance your seven chakras while listening to calming piano music or doing a guided meditation for positive energy and to clear your aura. You might meditate while listening to ASMR or an affirmation video with binaural beats that filter right into your subconscious. Today, you’re focused on the inner you.'),(32,'2022-12-21','week 1',8,'horoscope','This week, you see that you’re in a better place.<br>The week begins on Monday, December 19, with Venus in Capricorn and your house of transportation making a quincunx to Mars in Gemini and your house of traffic control. This is a challenging aspect if you need to get from point A to point B. Scorpio, there seem to be obstacles in the way, including construction, weather-related incidents, and hardworking cops trying to direct traffic. Today, you need to be patient if you’re in a vehicle.<br>On Wednesday, December 21, the sun in Sagittarius and your house of finances squares Jupiter in Pisces. Your income is likely to rise next year. Scorpio, you might have more confidence than you’ve had in a long time. You are developing skills and finding opportunities for gaining income or having more diversified revenue sources. Today, you could review your investments to see where you stand.'),(33,'2022-12-21','week 1',8,'horoscope','Santa’s Little Helpers have nothin’ on you, Scorpio! Well, not once magnanimous Jupiter swings back into Aries and your sixth house of service, systems and salubrious good health this Tuesday, December 20. Your inner elf is coming down from the shelf, eager to support everyone in your line of vision. But easy does it! The red-spotted planet holds court here until May 16, 2023, giving you more than six months to connect to outlets where your natural gifts intersect with the people who need them the most. If you’re thinking of volunteering, look for a place where you can show up ongoingly after you do a holiday season shift.<br>Since this is Jupiter’s second of two laps through Aries (the first was from May 10 to October 28), it’s possible that you’re already off to a running start here.<br>The sixth house is also the wellness domain, so speaking of running, vitality-boosting Jupiter in Aries could get you back on the trails, the treadmill or in tree pose on your yoga mat. Movement can and SHOULD be fun, as far as Jupiter’s concerned. Pick workouts or classes you love (or at least can say you honestly like) and commit to showing up regularly. For added motivation, pre-reward yourself with some cute sneakers or a Fitbit. When it comes to your day-to-day work, Jupiter could liberate you from the shackles of the 9-5 grind. While you need your security, Scorpio, who says you can\'t have more of it by being your own boss or working as an independent contractor? It may be time to set up that LLC and create the ethical, sustainable business model you haven’t been able to find anywhere else on the market.<br>If you’ve been more work than play, that all changes this Wednesday, December 21, when the Sun beams into Capricorn and sets off a four-week social whirlwind in your third house of friendship, communication and local activity. Between now and January 20, dial back your competitive streak and embrace the spirit of cooperation. Once you relax and let conversation flow freely (gingerbread lattes or martinis, optional), you could discover kindred spirits, project partners and ski buddies sitting right under your nose. One might even crop up on Friday, when the new supermoon in Capricorn opens your eyes to promising pals. All you have to do is keep yourself accessible—which might mean, consciously NOT intimidating. (This may take a little practice o’ cool one.) They could be coworkers, friends of friends, even people you see regularly at your go-to local venues. Small talk could add up to big plans if you take the time to break the ice.<br>Got an idea for a book, podcast or maybe a YouTube series? This media-savvy spell could bring some inspired keyboard strokes—or mic drops! Your intuitive sign has always been a thought-leader. Now it\'s time to get those ideas out of your head and into the zeitgeist. Some people may find your edgy ideas controversial, and that won\'t phase you much. Just try not to start a debate under the tree or while people are sipping champagne on NYE. There\'s a time and a place for everything!'),(34,'2022-12-21','week 1',8,'horoscope','If you’ve been backsliding on those habits you started in the spring, you’ll have the opportunity to get back on track when Jupiter reenters Aries, moving into your routine zone on Tuesday. You’re feeling healthy and ready to achieve anything. However, don’t get too cocky. It could lead to injury.<br>The solstice is the perfect time to get together with your friends, siblings and neighbors when the sun enters Capricorn, moving into your communication zone on Wednesday. Over the next four weeks you’ll be invited to plenty of social events that will keep you busy as you celebrate the holidays.<br>Friday is a perfect day for a holiday party during the new moon in Capricorn. After you finally cross everything off your holiday to-do list, invite your loved ones and neighbors over to celebrate the season with the people you care about most. Have some fun, Scorpio!'),(35,'2022-12-21','week 2',8,'horoscope','This week, you’re asking all the right questions.<br>On Tuesday, December 27, Venus in Capricorn and your house of siblings, cousins, and relatives around your age makes a semisextile to Saturn in Aquarius and your house of family. You might have a get-together planned with a sibling, but it would be quite easy for plans to go awry today. Scorpio, there could be delays based on your schedule, their schedule, or the weather in general. Today, flexibility will be key.<br>On Wednesday, December 28, Venus sextiles Neptune in Pisces and your house of romance. Today, you and your partner could do something really fun that makes you tingle all over. Scorpio, this might involve a couples massage or a steaming hot tub surrounded by snow. If you’re looking for love, this is a great day to find someone with romantic ideas. And the love that blossoms could be worthy of a romance novel.'),(36,'2022-12-21','week 1',9,'horoscope','This week, a good deed comes back threefold.<br>The week begins on Monday, December 19, with Venus in Capricorn and your house of shopping making a quincunx to Mars in Gemini and your house of relationships. Sagittarius, the thing that you wanted to get someone might not be available, at least not at the store you’re in. And now you’re scrambling to find this special item. It isn’t your fault. It’s possible there are supply-chain delays, or this is a very popular item this year. But now you might need to do a search both in town and online to find this precious gift.<br>On Wednesday, December 21, the sun in Sagittarius (happy birthday!) and your house of confidence squares Jupiter in Pisces. People around you seem to be going out of their way to compliment you. They have been watching your progress throughout the year, and friends and relatives are stepping up to say what a good job you’ve been doing. Sagittarius, these sentiments are genuine, so open your arms to receive them with joy.'),(37,'2022-12-21','week 1',9,'horoscope','Dress rehearsal is over, Sagittarius! Emerge from the green room and greet your adoring fans. It’s officially showtime (again) starting Tuesday, December 20, when your celestial stage director, live-out-loud Jupiter, swings back into Aries and turns on the house lights in your fifth house of fame, fertility and creative expression. Rise and shine and dress to impress! You might already have the wardrobe for it, in fact, since this is the second of Jupiter’s two laps through Aries. From May 10 to October 28, your red-spotted ruler rolled through the Ram’s realm. The only problem? Just as your star was starting to rise, Jupiter turned retrograde on July 28. But that’s all behind you now. For the coming six months, you can gain some REAL traction for your dreams, since Jupiter will barrel in forward motion through Aries for its entire sequel.<br>So, Sagittarius, where and how would you like to make a name for yourself? Reach out to friends or associates who might be able to help you get your creations into the public eye. Call reps, gallery owners, managers of open-mic nights. \"Art for art\'s sake\"\" is a nice concept but sharing it with the world is what you\'re ready for now. Plus'),(38,'2022-12-21','week 1',9,'horoscope','The year is almost over, Sagittarius, so let’s have some FUN this week! Jupiter reenters Aries on Tuesday, moving into your pleasure zone and giving you a major boost of luck and passion that will last for the next few months. You’ll be optimistic about love, life and your own talents, so dive headfirst into creative projects. Enjoy!<br>However, you’ll still have to do a little adulting when the sun enters Capricorn, moving into your value zone on Wednesday. Use the reflective nature of the year’s end to think about your self-worth. Value doesn’t come from how much you make but from how much you respect yourself.<br>End the week on a level-headed note during the new moon in Capricorn on Friday. Now is a great time to start looking into setting financial goals and even creating a budget for yourself, especially if you blew all your money on gifts.'),(39,'2022-12-21','week 2',9,'horoscope','This week, you’re keeping things in balance.<br>On Tuesday, December 27, Venus in Capricorn and your house of spending makes a semisextile to Saturn in Aquarius and your house of plans and spreadsheets. Today, there’s a little battle going on between your heart and your head. Your head knows what you’re spending limit is, has an idea of your budget, and knows what you would like to accomplish in the way of savings. But your heart might be pounding for a great new pair of designer sunglasses or a water bottle that includes a UV light to eradicate germs. Sagittarius, you’re struggling to stay on budget.<br>On Wednesday, December 28, Venus sextiles Neptune in Pisces and your house of dwellings. Today, you might be nesting. Sagittarius, it’s possible the weather outside makes it difficult to do anything else. You might want to stay home, snuggle up in a fleece blanket, and watch animated movies with your kids. Perhaps you want to do something a little bit old school and you’re putting together a jigsaw puzzle on the dining room table with your family.'),(40,'2022-12-21','week 1',10,'horoscope','This week, you’re focused on something old and something new.<br>The week begins on Monday, December 19, with Venus in Capricorn and your house of physical presence making a quincunx to Mars in Gemini and your house of well-being. Today, it would be quite easy to overdo it. Capricorn, you might stretch or bend the wrong way and suddenly feel like the Tin Man from The Wizard of Oz. Today, start slowly and build the momentum. Jumping into something is not advised.<br>On Wednesday, December 21, the sun in Sagittarius and your house of spirituality squares Jupiter in Pisces. You might be feeling very connected to the Universe. Capricorn, you could be lighting candles and asking for blessings for your family and friends. You could attend a spiritual service or celebrate Yule, the ancient holiday of the winter solstice. This is a good day to put out an offering of fruits, nuts, and seeds for the wild animals in the neighborhood.'),(41,'2022-12-21','week 1',10,'horoscope','When Charles Dickens wrote, “Charity begins in the home and justice begins next door,” he might as well have been picturing the next six months for Capricorns. Generous, curious Jupiter comes in for a landing this Tuesday, December 20, returning to trailblazing Aries and your domestic fourth house until May 16, 2023. While you may feel like planting deeper roots, you’ll also be curious about what’s happening beyond your own welcome mat. Are you ready to get outright neighborly, Capricorn? Sure you could show up at people’s doors with fresh-baked cookies, but don’t stop there. Become a regular presence at city council meetings or put in some volunteer shifts at an impactful neighborhood charity. A deeper level of involvement will help you feel “at home” in your area. Such efforts may already be underway for many Sea Goats. Jupiter already passed through Aries from May 10 to October 28 of this year. But once it turned retrograde on July 28, progress likely hit some speed bumps. Happily, Jupiter remains in direct motion for its second (and final) trek through Aries.<br>Tend to matters behind your own front door, too. You\'ll be in the mood for creature comforts and the stabilizing effect of coming home to the same bed every night. Of course, there\'s always the possibility that you could blend these two energies in a creative way, like giving the digital nomad lifestyle a whirl or literally moving to a new home that suits 2023 Capricorn. Jupiter hungers for adventure, so if travel or a relocation isn\'t in the cards, look for other ways to scratch that itch like starting a kitchen-table business or turning a corner of your home into a maker’s studio. On a more personal level, this Jupiter cycle will spotlight family relationships. If you\'ve been holding your tongue about something, possibly for years, you\'ll be supported in broaching the subject now. But go in gently! Candid Jupiter in this emo realm can have the effect of a firehose and you don’t want to overwhelm anyone with intensity when you’re simply trying to heal a rift.<br>Holiday celebrations segue seamlessly into birthday celebrations as the Sun blazes into your sign on Wednesday, December 21, officially kicking off Capricorn season 2022. No need to keep the reserve bubbly on ice until NYE. Pour a couple flutes—or mix up some killer mocktails—to toast winter solstice and The Festival of Capricorn simultaneously. Or wait until Friday’s new supermoon in Capricorn, which marks your astrological New Year, another reason to celebrate YOU.<br>Over the coming four weeks, you\'ll be a force of nature, easily attracting opportunity and winning hearts and minds. With Mercury, Venus and magnetic Pluto sharing the Sun\'s flight path through Capricorn this week—and the moon lingering in your sign until early Christmas Day, anything you cook up could go viral. Your sign is the most future-oriented of them all, so don’t bother waiting until January 1 to get in a visionary groove. Go ahead and create a wish list of your objectives for 2023 now. This is also a fine idea because (sad trombone) Mercury WILL be going retrograde from December 29 to January 18. So you might as well get a running start on this while your head is clear. Whether it’s a wish list, first draft mission statement or half-done vision board, keep it somewhere you can see it and re-motivate yourself every day. Then, plan to pick it up again with the first new moon of 2023, on January 21. Do you need some support in reaching your objectives? Hiring a career coach, taking a master class or an experiential vacation are smart investments in yourself—especially if you can parlay them into a salary increase as you gain new skills.'),(42,'2022-12-21','week 1',10,'horoscope','Home is where the heart is this holiday season, especially when Jupiter enters Aries, moving into your family zone on Tuesday. As we get cozy in winter, this is a great opportunity to look for a new home, make some renovations or even add a new family member. Keep an open mind.<br>The rest of the week brings a major boost of self-esteem and confidence when the sun enters your sign on Wednesday, ushering us into your season. This is the season for your success. If you want to be the GOAT, Capricorn, you’d better start dressing and acting like one.<br>Especially during the new moon in your sign on Friday. You are feeling your best self right now, so use it to your full advantage. This is a great time to go on first dates, start a new job or take the first steps in creating the life you’ve always dreamed of.'),(43,'2022-12-21','week 2',10,'horoscope','This week, you’re in the spotlight.<br>On Tuesday, December 27, Venus in your own sign of Capricorn makes a semisextile to your ruler Saturn in Aquarius and your house of material gain. Everything feels better when you keep good track of your money. Capricorn, you might sometimes resist the principles of accounting, but you always feel more grounded and stronger in general when you know what you have and what you need. Today is a good day to put your finances in order.<br>On Wednesday, December 28, Venus sextiles Neptune in Pisces and your house of fiction, scripts, and creative writing. Capricorn, you might take a pen in hand and write a short story. You could find a friend to collaborate with on a screenplay. Or maybe you are filling in a journal that has writing prompts guiding you to focus on gratitude and success. Today, you’re getting your thoughts on paper.'),(44,'2022-12-21','week 1',11,'horoscope','This week, you’re finding the answers you seek.<br>The week begins on Monday, December 19, with Venus in Capricorn and your house of rest and recuperation making a quincunx to Mars in Gemini and your house of fun and excitement. Today, you could be a little tired because of all the excitement and activities you’ve been doing. Aquarius, you might need more rest, but you don’t want to miss a moment of the fun. Today, you might be moving forward and promising yourself that you will nap later.<br>On Wednesday, December 21, the sun in Sagittarius and your house of friendships squares Jupiter in Pisces. Aquarius, you might be getting together with a large group of friends or people who could be potential friends. You might have a party in a public venue where suddenly you have many more people around you, and everyone is laughing and talking and having a good time. If you’re single, this is a great day to go to a singles’ mixer and meet some new people.'),(45,'2022-12-21','week 1',11,'horoscope','Stop! Don’t buy that pricey, overseas flight ticket…yet. Not until you take in this news. On Tuesday, December 20, high-key Jupiter sails back into Aries, turbo-charging your third house of local activity with its adventurous beams. We’re not saying global travel should go off the menu, but we ARE saying that another lonely off-grid quest is the last thing your soon-to-be-social-again sign needs. While the red-spotted planet splashes back into Aries for the second of its two laps, the real action is happening closer to home than you might even realize. Between now and May 16, 2023, you’ll have the best time when you hang out in nearby venues, not simply to enjoy the offerings, but to be part of shaping the area’s culture. Round up a few friends and become a regular at some neighborhood haunts or if you’re feeling ambitious, propose an idea for a pop-up event at one of your favorite boutiques, bars or cafes.<br>A potential fringe benefit for single Water Bearers: You could meet a very hot prospect who lives within walking distance or a short commute away. But with free-spirited Jupiter in this primarily platonic zone, FWBs might be as committed as you’d like to get. Coupled Aquarians should make a point of getting out together more often. An infusion of cultural activities—not to mention the energy of shared friends—can resuscitate your attraction. But if a relationship is truly gasping for air, candid Jupiter can help you ease into a new “let’s just be friends” situation that is the best for both of you.<br>Since the third house also rules transportation, you might want to invest in a new set of wheels in the coming months, whether two or four. With jetsetting Jupiter here, you could be logging a lot of road miles, and you need a reliable ride. To make your commuting more pleasurable AND productive, upgrade your gadgetry (no more cracked screens!), tune in to intriguing podcasts or make a practice of learning new words of a foreign language with every ride. Who knows? With the planet of publishing in this communicative zone, you may be inspired to plug in the mic to start a broadcast of your own.<br>Give yourself a minute to ramp up to this social state. Wednesday is the winter solstice, when the shortest, darkest day of the year announces the beginning of Capricorn season. Until January 20, the Sun will be nestled in your restorative twelfth house, the time before your birthday each year where you need to recharge your batteries. On Friday, the new moon in Capricorn—a potent supermoon—doubles down on this sleepy energy. Take lots of disco naps and revel in the fact that \"pajama dressing\"\" can be passed off as couture. Whenever possible'),(46,'2022-12-21','week 1',11,'horoscope','It’s the most social time of the year for you, Aquarius, as Jupiter reenters Aries, moving back into your communication zone on Tuesday. This is a period of bright, vibrant ideas that you can work to turn into reality. Attend big events to share your ideas with others or start a study group.<br>However, you won’t be feeling too chatty when the sun enters Capricorn, moving into your privacy zone on Wednesday. The ghosts of your past come out on the longest night of the year, and you could be a little more sensitive than usual. Get ready for winter by taking the time to retreat and heal yourself for the new year.<br>While it is the holidays, you’re not really in the spirit during the new moon in Capricorn on Friday. It’s the season of giving, and you might be making plenty of sacrifices that can leave you feeling a bit raw.'),(47,'2022-12-21','week 2',11,'horoscope','This week, you’re getting something you want.<br>On Tuesday, December 27, Venus in Capricorn makes a semisextile to Saturn in your own sign of Aquarius and your house of confidence. Today, you might be the person who’s in front of the room holding a microphone. You might feel unprepared for this, but you’re up for adventure and excitement. Aquarius, this impromptu stardom could come because someone else is unavailable, and now it’s up to you to step up on stage and take the lead.<br>On Wednesday, December 28, Venus sextiles Neptune in Pisces and your house of finances. Today, what you want seems to be on sale. Aquarius, you can find a very good deal on anything from a down coat to a designer purse. You can find the electronic device you’re looking for at a lower price than you were expecting. And while the extra spending on accessories could ultimately put you over budget, you can fulfill a wish today.'),(48,'2022-12-21','week 1',12,'horoscope','This week, you’re giving and receiving.<br>The week begins on Monday, December 19, with Venus in Capricorn and your house of friendships making a quincunx to Mars in Gemini and your house of family. Today, you need to be in two places at once, but since you don’t have a Star Trek transporter, you might have to disappoint someone. It’s possible that you have friends who want to see you, a child in the school play, and a family member who needs help with holiday preparations. Today is a busy day, but you’ll probably have to pass on at least one social event.<br>On Wednesday, December 21, the sun in Sagittarius and your house of recognition squares Jupiter in Pisces. You could receive some accolades from your supervisor at work. They might give you a lovely card and possibly a gift to show their appreciation for all your hard work. If you’re looking for a new job, you could receive an offer at this time.'),(49,'2022-12-21','week 1',12,'horoscope','Approaching max capacity? Ever since supersizer Jupiter dove into Pisces May 13, 2021, you’ve been expanding in every direction. (And we’re betting you’ve got money in the bank to show for it!) The magnanimous planet has been weaving in and out of your sign ever since, making it impossible to tame your expansion. But that level of exponential growth can only be sustained for so long before you need to hit the brakes and integrate the progress. Good news! You’ll get six months to do exactly that beginning this Tuesday, December 20, when Jupiter waves its final farewell to Pisces and leaves your sign until 2033. Now, the red-spotted maximizer planet is bound for Aries, where it powers forward through your second house of daily income and routines for six whole months. It’s been fun stretching PAST your limits in groundbreaking (and, at times, exhausting) ways. But as one of the zodiac’s emotional water signs, you crave a measure of security—even if you’re repeating a comforting routine on a daily basis. Between now and May 16, 2023, you can get your fins back on terra firma and lay a new, more solid financial foundation.<br>With abundant Jupiter in this money zone, it’s prime time to focus on your professional aspirations, set intentions and start to manifest them, because you\'ve got a cosmic tailwind at your back. What are your goals—a soul-satisfying new job (or just a super-well-paying one?), launching your own brand, saving enough for a new car or a home upgrade? Whatever the case, you\'ll probably welcome a bit more stability in the first half of 2023. Since Jupiter rules education and advanced training, you might consider adding some tools to your kit or bringing your skills up to date by taking some workshops, webinars or formal classes. When it comes to your hard-earned cash, stay mindful. What good is making more if you burn it as fast as you earn it?  <br>Don’t take fun off the menu! You couldn’t if you tried starting this Wednesday, when the Sun heads into Capricorn and swings from the chandeliers of your popularity-boosting eleventh house until January 20. And when the new supermoon in Capricorn brings a second boost on Friday, you’ll be the ringmaster of reindeer games. Don ye now that festive apparel, especially your dancing shoes. With invites flooding in, you’ve got four solid weeks to circulate and reconnect with all the people you’ve been too busy to see. Drop in with a plate of cookies, then organize back-to-yoga wellness reboots for friends after January 1.<br>The more will be the merrier for the coming four weeks, but that can present yet another dilemma: Where to spend your time...and with who? As the holidays draw near, you can’t keep putting off decisions about where to celebrate. You need to make a ruling ASAP! There are plenty of ways to contribute if you don’t want to host—like playing entertainment director or offering to DJ with one of your otherworldly playlists.\n'),(50,'2022-12-21','week 1',12,'horoscope','End the year on a lucky note when Jupiter reenters Aries, moving into your value zone on Tuesday. The investments you made last spring are finally coming to fruition. From financial windfalls to self-esteem, just make sure you don’t spend all your good fortune in one place.<br>Especially as you’ll be thinking about the future when the sun enters Capricorn, moving into your social zone on Wednesday. As we get closer to 2023, this is an excellent time to think about your hopes and dreams. Use this time to make the right connections to make the new year easy and productive.<br>End the week on a social note during the new moon in Capricorn on Friday. Ring in the holiday season by spending time with your close friends and loved ones. This is a great time to enjoy some holiday activities and make some memories, Pisces.'),(51,'2022-12-21','week 2',12,'horoscope','This week, you’re intuitive about almost everything.<br>On Tuesday, December 27, Venus in Capricorn and your house of friendships makes a semisextile to Saturn in Aquarius and your house of charitable endeavors. Pisces, you might join a friend to help out at a local shelter, food bank, or the nonprofit community theater in your neighborhood. This is a good day to do something to give back to the community.<br>On Wednesday, December 28, Venus sextiles Neptune in your own sign of Pisces and your house of physical presence. You are turning heads today. Everyone is saying how attractive you look and how great your outfit is. Pisces, you’re putting your best foot forward, so this is a good day to meet new friends. If you’re looking for love, this is an excellent time to go on a first date, even if you’ve only just started communicating via text.');
